Description: Neck sherd of large East Greek Middle Wild Goat II pottery krater with turn to lip; dull orange clay with white inclusions; slipped cream inside and out; exterior: part of a wild goat to left; filling ornaments: dots and rosettes; broad band painted at top of wall.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.1194)
